{{2014 Southland Conference football standings}}
The '''2014 Central Arkansas Bears football team''' represented the [[University of Central Arkansas]] in the [[2014 NCAA Division I FCS football season]]. The Bears were led by first-year head coach [[Steve Campbell (American football)|Steve Campbell]] and played their home games at [[Estes Stadium]]. They are a member of the [[Southland Conference]].  The Bears finished the season 6–6 overall and 5–3 in conference play to finish in a three way tie for third place.

